node.text:
WE CAN STOP THIS. 🙏🏼 One of the main barriers that undermine access to prevention and treatment services is stigma and discrimination, which is still pervasive in healthcare settings, at home, at work and in society. Many people are not accessing services out of fear of being recognised or judged or out of personal safety and security. WE MUST CHANGE THIS.

These are trying times; we must not lose sight of the goals and ensure #HIV remains a key priority issue. Together we can, together we are stronger, together we can end #AIDS.

PLEASE SIGN the letter and join us in asking world leaders to fulfil their commitments to ending AIDS as a public health threat by 2030. Visit 👉🏼 www.unaids.org for more info.

@unaids_ap @unaidsglobal @loveyourself.ph

node.title: AIDS is not over, but it can be.

I used to be a person that didn't put much thought into my nutrition and recovery. But all that changed this year. I've been more aware of  my health and what my body can do. Especially this year, we don't want that.  
Every time I endorse a brand I always make sure it works, that I believe in it and that I use it in real life. That’s why before I accepted being 4Life Philippines brand ambassador I made  sure  I’ve used their  products first for a few months before partnering with them.   I'm really happy with the results and I feel great! @4lifephilippinesofficial is popularly known as the immune system company. They are based in the US and  have been manufacturing supplements for the past  22 years.   That is why I'm thrilled to announce my partnership as 4Life Philippines first brand ambassador. In the coming months, I'll be sharing more about their products like the Transfer Factor. It's backed up by research and I've also done my personal research about it. Really excited to share more about it with you.   Also, another thing I love about 4Life is their passion for helping children all over their world through their service pillar "Foundation 4Life". node.text:
A glimpse at Indigenous Futurism 🇵🇭

For me, this is Philippine indi-GENIUS! We focus and shine the light on our weavers from Lih'han Di Immipugo of Kiangan, Ifugao @lihhan_di_immipugo. This is a look at our culture into the future: of what could have been, and what it could still be. There is much to see and learn —  from our ever-evolving culture, from every Filipino’s heART and soul. Everything is intertwined and in fashion, it’s inspiring when different creatives come together — from weavers to designers to artists to photographers. New stories arise from each concept piece, each photo output.

I hope this doesn’t end with us just feeling inspired. It’s a start though. I hope we will always support each other’s artistry and creativity. I hope we can learn to preserve and continue traditions so we can weave them into our future. 

It is with pride that I can wear my country’s stories as pieces of art. I hope every Filipino does too! 💙🇵🇭

📸 @mjsuayan
